## 2. Offset Functions: LAG / LEAD

`LAG()` looks backward; `LEAD()` looks forward.

```sql
SELECT
  month, revenue,
  LAG(revenue, 1) OVER (ORDER BY month) AS prev_month_revenue,
  revenue - LAG(revenue, 1) OVER (ORDER BY month) AS revenue_change
FROM monthly_sales;
```

| month | revenue | prev_month_revenue | revenue_change |
|---|---|---|---|
| Jan | 1000 | NULL | NULL |
| Feb | 1200 | 1000 | 200 |
| Mar | 900 | 1200 | -300 |

Signature: `LAG(column, offset, default_value)`
- `offset` — how many rows back/forward (default 1)
- `default_value` — value to use if no such row exists (instead of `NULL`)

