## 3. Aggregate Functions as Window Functions

Any aggregate (`SUM`, `AVG`, `COUNT`, `MIN`, `MAX`) becomes a window function when you add `OVER (...)`.

### Running Total

```sql
SELECT
  order_date, amount,
  SUM(amount) OVER (ORDER BY order_date) AS running_total
FROM orders;
```

| order_date | amount | running_total |
|---|---|---|
| Jan 1 | 100 | 100 |
| Jan 2 | 50 | 150 |
| Jan 3 | 200 | 350 |

### Percent of Total

```sql
SELECT
  category, sales,
  ROUND(100.0 * sales / SUM(sales) OVER (), 2) AS pct_of_total
FROM category_sales;
```

`SUM(sales) OVER ()` with no `PARTITION BY` computes a grand total repeated on every row.

### Percent of Group Total

```sql
SELECT
  region, category, sales,
  ROUND(100.0 * sales / SUM(sales) OVER (PARTITION BY region), 2) AS pct_of_region
FROM category_sales;
```

