## 4. FIRST_VALUE / LAST_VALUE / NTH_VALUE

```sql
SELECT
  employee_id, department, salary,
  FIRST_VALUE(salary) OVER (
    PARTITION BY department ORDER BY salary DESC
  ) AS highest_in_dept
FROM employees;
```

> **Gotcha:** `LAST_VALUE()` needs an explicit frame to work as expected — by default the frame ends at the current row, so `LAST_VALUE` often just returns the current row's own value. Fix with:
```sql
LAST_VALUE(salary) OVER (
  PARTITION BY department ORDER BY salary DESC
  ROWS BETWEEN UNBOUNDED PRECEDING AND UNBOUNDED FOLLOWING
) AS lowest_in_dept
```

